      "sin⁻¹(-x) = -sin⁻¹x but cos⁻¹(-x) = π - cos⁻¹x (opposite signs, different formulas!)",
      "sin⁻¹x + cos⁻¹x = π/2 — most frequently tested identity",
      "tan⁻¹x + tan⁻¹y formula changes when xy > 1 (add π for positive x,y)",
